						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in front of the Rāmasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record can be assigned to 9th century A.D., on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged. However, it starts with the usual <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the Vaiduṁbas and seems to register the gift of a village Kōḷavaḷḷi and refers to Kaṟetyēḍla Sabbeye, Kāla • ggaya raṭṭaḍi as witnesses of the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
